genresAdvancedInfo.name: rap catarinense
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rap catarinense is a subgenre of rap music that originated in the state of Santa Catarina, Brazil. It is characterized by its use of the Brazilian Portuguese language and its incorporation of local cultural elements into the music. The lyrics often address social and political issues, and the beats are typically influenced by Brazilian funk and samba.
